        <p style="font-family: Montserrat;">Beginning on June 14, 2020, Ace Airlines began assembling its new Level 6 rated flight simulator. Now, today, it is finished. It is a Level 6 rated fully enclosed flight simulator. It is complete with every instrument, switch, button, and lever that would be in the actual airplane. It is based on a 1984 Cessna 172P. It will be used to train new Ace Airlines pilots. "This new flight simulator will be a valuable tool in teaching new pilots." Ben Lambertson said. The current plan is to update the sim to a Level D flight simulator in the coming months. As part of this new sim the Ace Airlines Simulation website has also been updated. There you will be able to see the progress of the sim, as well as pictures and videos of the sim.</p>

